# ── runoff_model .gitignore ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HARD RULE: code only, NEVER data.
# No client / EFM / DAV data and no pipeline outputs may ever be committed.
# Real data lives ONLY on the work PC and never leaves it.

# Python bytecode / caches
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Pipeline outputs & frozen artifacts (all regenerated by the code)
_out/
_artifacts/
_run/

# Built panels / synthetic data fixtures (regenerated by synth_dav_files.py)
_synth/

# viz.py self-test SVG outputs
_viz_test/

# profile_dav.py output — describes the real client schema on the work PC
profile_report.txt

# Data file types — defense-in-depth: a stray data file outside the dirs
# above still cannot be staged.
*.csv
*.xls
*.xlsx
*.xlsm
*.parquet
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.gz
*.zip

# ...EXCEPT the hand-authored macro-episode calendar: it's a curated INPUT
# the pipeline reads (regime_calendar.py), public documented episodes, not
# client data. It must travel with the code.
!src/data/regime_events.csv

# Editor / OS / misc junk
.Rhistory
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/
